.TH LINUXUSBCREATOR 1 "July 2026" "Linux USB Creator 0.5.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
linuxusbcreator \- inspect USB devices and write verified raw images
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B linuxusbcreator
.br
.B linuxusbcreator --diagnose
.br
.B linuxusbcreator --sha256
.I IMAGE
.br
.B linuxusbcreator --inspect-image
.I IMAGE
.br
.B linuxusbcreator --inspect-windows
.I IMAGE
.br
.B linuxusbcreator --validate-windows
.I IMAGE
.br
.B linuxusbcreator --write-windows
.I IMAGE DEVICE SERIAL SIZE
.BI --firmware " uefi|bios"
.br
.B linuxusbcreator --write-image
.I IMAGE DEVICE SERIAL SIZE
.RI [ --no-verify ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Linux USB Creator discovers removable storage through UDisks2. Raw image writes
are performed by a short-lived Polkit helper; the graphical process is never
run as root.
.PP
When started without options, the graphical interface selects a local ISO/raw
image and an eligible USB target, requires destructive confirmation, and shows
write and read-back verification percentages. Supported Windows installers
offer UEFI/GPT and, for compatible x64 images, BIOS/MBR; both use FAT32.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --diagnose
Print detected devices and their eligibility as JSON.
.TP
.BI --sha256 " IMAGE"
Compute SHA-256 for a regular image file.
.TP
.BI --inspect-image " IMAGE"
Inspect the image contents and classify them as Linux, Windows, or raw/unknown.
For recognized ISO installers, print the distribution family and architecture
as JSON. This command never writes a device.
.TP
.BI --inspect-windows " IMAGE"
Inspect an ISO9660/UDF Windows installer without privileges and print its boot
architectures, install payload and FAT32 compatibility as JSON. This command
never writes a device.
.TP
.BI --validate-windows " IMAGE"
Mount an ISO through a read-only, autoclearing UDisks2 loop and validate both
the boot WIM and install WIM/ESD using wimlib. The loop is unmounted and removed
before the command exits.
.TP
.BI --write-windows " IMAGE DEVICE SERIAL SIZE --firmware uefi|bios"
Destroy the confirmed removable USB device and create Windows installation
media. The ISO is mounted read-only and validated before the helper creates
UEFI/GPT/FAT32 or BIOS/MBR/FAT32. BIOS is accepted only for images containing
the x64 legacy boot structure. Files are copied without privileges; an
oversized install.wim is divided into install.swm fragments with wimlib. The
fragments and all copied files are verified before the target is unmounted.
.TP
.BI --write-image " IMAGE DEVICE SERIAL SIZE"
Destroy the contents of the confirmed removable USB device and write IMAGE.
SERIAL and SIZE must match the immediately preceding diagnostic result. Full
read-back SHA-256 verification is enabled by default.
.TP
.B --no-verify
Skip read-back verification. This is not recommended.
.TP
.B --version
Print the program version.
.SH SAFETY
The helper rejects partitions, non-USB media, non-removable or read-only media,
active swap, mounted filesystems after unmounting, changed serial or capacity,
and the current system/root disk. For Windows media the helper performs only
one of the two fixed partitioning preparations; ISO parsing, copying, and WIM processing stay
in the unprivileged process.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/log/linuxusbcreator.jsonl
Root-owned structured operation log.
.SH AUTHOR
Víctor Díaz Gonzalez.
